GreenPad Help
=============

Overview
--------
GreenPad is a lightweight Unicode text editor for Windows.
It aims to be a practical Notepad replacement with minimal footprint.

  * Full Unicode support (BMP + supplementary planes via surrogate pairs)
  * Proportional and fixed-width font support
  * Syntax highlighting via .kwd keyword files
  * Regular expression search (PCRE2 when pcre2-16.dll is present)
  * Wide character encoding support (see "Character Encodings" below)
  * Multilingual UI: English, Japanese, Korean, Chinese (Simplified/Traditional),
    Russian (language auto-detected from Windows display language)

Original author: k.inaba
Extended by: roytam1, RamonUnch
This build: modernised 64-bit fork (Windows Vista+ x64).

Source: https://github.com/Aile2017/GreenPad


Keyboard Shortcuts
------------------

File
  Ctrl+N              New file
  Ctrl+O              Open...
  Ctrl+R              ReOpen (change encoding)
  Ctrl+L              Open elevated (UAC)
  Alt+Enter           ReOpen (same as Ctrl+R)
  Ctrl+S              Save
  Ctrl+Shift+S        Save As...
  F12                 Save As...
  F5                  Reload file (keeps cursor position)
  Ctrl+P              Print...
  Ctrl+E              Save and Exit
  Ctrl+Shift+E        Discard and Exit
  Ctrl+F4             Exit
  Esc                 Quick Exit (prompts if unsaved)

Edit
  Ctrl+Z              Undo
  Ctrl+Y              Redo
  Ctrl+X / Shift+Del  Cut
  Ctrl+C / Ctrl+Ins   Copy
  Ctrl+V / Shift+Ins  Paste
  Del                 Delete selection
  Ctrl+A              Select all
  F6                  Insert date & time
  Ctrl+I              Insert Unicode code point
  Tab                 Indent selection (multi-line)
  Shift+Tab           Unindent selection (multi-line)
  Ctrl+K              Delete to end of line
  Ctrl+U              Delete to start of line
  Ctrl+Shift+K        Delete to end of file
  Ctrl+Shift+U        Delete to start of file

Modify (Edit > Modify)
  Alt+U               Upper case selection
  Alt+L               Lower case selection
  Alt+I               Invert case selection
  Alt+R               Reduce to ASCII (replace non-ASCII with '?')
  Alt+W               Trim trailing spaces
  Alt+Z               Strip first character of each selected line
  Alt+A               Strip last character of each selected line
  Alt+Q               Quote (add comment character to each selected line)
  Alt+N               Unquote (remove comment character)
  Ctrl+\              External filter...

Search
  Ctrl+F              Find / Replace
  Ctrl+H              Find / Replace (same dialog)
  F3                  Find next
  F2                  Find previous
  Shift+F3            Find previous
  Ctrl+J              Jump to line (supports: 543  +10  3,8  etc.)
  Ctrl+G              External grep
  F7                  Open selection as file path or URL
  F8                  Show selection length in status bar
  Ctrl+B              Go to matching brace / bracket / quote

View
  Ctrl+1              No wrapping
  Ctrl+2              Wrap at fixed character width
  Ctrl+3              Wrap at window right edge
  Ctrl+Up             Zoom in
  Ctrl+Down           Zoom out
  Ctrl+0              Reset zoom to 100%

Window
  Ctrl+Tab            Next GreenPad window
  Ctrl+Shift+Tab      Previous GreenPad window

Help
  F1                  Context help (opens HelpExe with current file info)


Command Line
------------
  greenpad [-r] [-l<line>] [-c<charset>] [-e<locale>] [<file> ...]

  -r              Open in read-only mode
  -l<line>        Scroll to line number (e.g. -l543)
  -c<charset>     Override character encoding (see codes below)
  -e<locale>      Override UI language (e.g. -eja-JP, -ezh-CN)
  -lang <locale>  Same as -e but as a separate argument

  Multiple -l/-c/-<file> triplets can be given to open several files.

  Example:
    greenpad -l543 -c932 readme.txt
    Opens readme.txt as Shift_JIS and scrolls to line 543.


Character Encodings
-------------------
Use the code with -c on the command line (prefix the number with -c, no space).
The same codes appear in the ReOpen dialog's encoding combo box.

Unicode / ISO
  Auto-detect           0       (default; BOM and heuristic detection)
  UTF-8                -65001   (no BOM)
  UTF-8 (BOM)           65001
  UTF-16 BE            -5       (no BOM)
  UTF-16 BE (BOM)      -3
  UTF-16 LE            -6       (no BOM)
  UTF-16 LE (BOM)      -4
  UTF-32 BE            -9       (no BOM)
  UTF-32 BE (BOM)      -7
  UTF-32 LE            -10      (no BOM)
  UTF-32 LE (BOM)      -8
  UTF-7                 65000
  UTF-1                -1
  UTF-1 (BOM)          -64999
  UTF-5                -2
  UTF-5 (BOM)          -14
  UTF-9 (1997)         -11
  UTF-9 (1997, BOM)    -65002
  UTF-EBCDIC           -15
  UTF-EBCDIC (BOM)     -16
  SCSU                 -60002
  SCSU (BOM)           -60000
  BOCU-1               -60003
  BOCU-1 (BOM)         -60001
  FSS-UTF (1992)       -12
  FSS-UTF (1992, BOM)  -13
  ASCII                 20127

Japanese
  Shift_JIS (Windows)   932
  EUC-JP               -932
  ISO-2022-JP          -933
  x-mac-japanese        10001

Korean
  EUC-KR / UHC          949
  ISO-2022-KR          -950
  Johab                 1361
  x-mac-korean          10003

Chinese (Simplified)
  GB18030               54936   (no BOM)
  GB18030 (BOM)        -54936
  GBK / GB2312          936
  ISO-2022-CN          -936
  HZ-GB2312            -937
  x-mac-prc             10008

Chinese (Traditional)
  Big5                  950
  EUC-TW / CNS          20000
  TCA                   20001
  ETen (Big5-HKSCS)     20002
  IBM 5550              20003
  Teletext              20004
  Wang                  20005
  x-mac-taiwan          10002

Western European
  Windows-1252          1252
